Package au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.graph.node

Class HasEdges

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.QueryAdaptor
      • au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.graph.node.HasEdges
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Queryable
    public class HasEdges
extends QueryAdaptor

    Check if a Node has Edges that satisfy some constraints like a Query, a class Id, a multiplicity.

    Type of input to submit()
    Node
    Type of result
    same as input (result=input)
    Fails if
    input edge list filtered by a query on node, a query on edges, an edge class id, an edge direction, does not match the multiplicity passed to the constructor
    Author:
    Shayne Flint - 2/4/2012
    refactored by Jacques Gignoux - 4/10/2021
    See Also:
    CoreQueries.hasEdges(...), CoreQueries.hasInEdges(...), CoreQueries.hasOutEdges(...)
